                                Report abuseTranscript of The Success Story of Mark AlbersThe Success Story of Petroleum Engineer Mark AlbersBy Ben CalkinsFrom Australia he was promoted to supervise the oil process's in Africa, Chad, Nigeria, Alaska and Texas. This is where he devoloped the nickname, the main oil guy of the western world.In 1991 he was transferred to Australia which he was overseeing major oil transactions. He excelled here which opened the door to promotions.Mark Albers started his career when he graduated from Texas A&M University.Mr. Albers received his Bachelors in Petroleum Engineering with high honors.He joined the Exxon Mobil team in 1979 which started his very successful career. He began as an entry level Petroleum Engineer.In 2001 he was the Vice President of Exxon Mobil. He did this by being exceptionally well at his previous position.Then in 2004 he took the position to become the president of Exxon Mobil Gas. Some would say at this point he was the most powerful man that controlled the flow of oil.At this point his totally salary was $11,657,713. This includes wages, stock shares and compensationIn 2007 he became the new Senior Vice President of Exxon Mobil Gas.Fun Facts- He is on the board of directors or a member of 6 different organizations - Exxon Mobil is the largest supplier of oil throughout the world- He once was ranked by Forbes as being part of the top 100,000 most powerful people in the worldMark Albers started as an entry level engineer but with a good work ethic he rose up to become the President of the company. Texas A&M is the top ranked school for Petroleum EngineeringMany petroleum engineers have to to travel to oversee the operations of the drilling sitesHe was an intern which enabled him in getting a job offer right out of collegeHere he developed new innovative ways to extract oil offshoreThis liquid gold can be found in many locations across the globe.Here is a picture of Mr. Albers meeting with the president of ExxonHere Mr. Albers is adressing the world about clean and efficient energyPetroleum Engineers have one of the highest salaries throughout all the occupations.An example of his careerFull transcriptMore presentations by
    
        
